MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: (^|/)CLAUDE\.md$
MATCH_CONTENT: (^#{2,4}\s+[A-Z]|NEVER|ALWAYS|^\*\*|MUST( not)?\s|[Dd]on't\s|[Dd]o not\s|should never)
ADVISORY: |
  Before adding or modifying a rule in CLAUDE.md, apply the placement rubric:

    "What's the smallest directory where violating this rule actually causes harm?"

  That's the file it belongs in. The hierarchy in this repo:

    /CLAUDE.md                                  ← monorepo-wide (tech stack, commands)
    /apps/<app>/CLAUDE.md                       ← app-wide (cross-shell, cross-surface)
    /apps/client/src/shells/<shell>/CLAUDE.md   ← shell-specific conventions

  Telltale signs a rule is misplaced (belongs deeper):
    - References a UI element only one shell has ("Today tab", "Cast Strip")
    - Hard-codes values that have a shell-specific constant nearby
      (e.g., z-index 70 when PULSE_Z.reveal exists)
    - Says "use library X" when shells diverge on that choice
    - References a file path under a shell directory

  When in doubt, place deeper. A rule in a shell's CLAUDE.md only loads for
  agents working in that shell's directory tree — it can't create false
  positives elsewhere. A rule in apps/client/CLAUDE.md fires for every
  client session regardless of which shell the agent is working on.

  Existing per-shell CLAUDE.md files (as of 2026-04-14):
    apps/client/src/shells/pulse/CLAUDE.md
    apps/client/src/shells/vivid/CLAUDE.md
    apps/client/src/shells/classic/CLAUDE.md

  Real cost avoided: stale Vivid-specific rules at the client app level
  ("Results inline, not fullscreen" + legacy z-index stack) were wrongly
  cited against a Pulse design spec that explicitly prescribed a full-screen
  cartridge overlay, producing a bogus review blocker.
